In view of the strengthening of the two right-wing populist parties – the Austrian Freedom Party (FPÖ) had previously won 18% of the votes and the BZÖ had won 11% of the votes – the Social Democrats, however, expressed their fears about the re-unification of the European Union with the BZ<0xC3><0x89>P in the year of 1999 (when the EPP agreed on a common government).
